<section>
  <title>Exam rules</title>

<ol>
<li>You must bring your University ID card.</li>
<li>You are allowed 50 minutes to take the exam.</li>
<li>You are allowed to have one-half of one letter (8.5in <m>\times</m> 11in) sized sheet of paper of handwritten notes.  Double-sided is OK.</li>
<li>You are allowed to have a scientific calculator in the exam.  However, graphing calculators are NOT allowed on this exam. </li>
<li>No textbook or electronic equipment (other than scientific calculator) allowed.</li>

</ol>
</section>

<section>
  <title>Exam format</title>

  <p>The exam will be taken on iPads and will essentially look like the practice exam, except that you will not be given feedback on your responses.</p>
  
  <p>You can change your response to each question as often as you like.  Your last response for each question at the time you submit exam will be the one that is graded.</p>

  <p>The exam will not tell you which questions you got right or wrong.  However, immediately after taking the exam, you can go to the gradebook and click on the Integration Exam to see your score and the solutions to the problems.</p>
</section>



